00071 bool Add_Gate(Circuit& circuit,GateType type, char *name,char* output,char **inputs,int numSignals)
00072 {
00073     Gate *gate = new Gate(name,type);
00074     map<string,Wire *>::iterator iter;
00075 
00076     // Some consistency checks before we add
00077     // the wires to the gates inputs and output
00078     // 1. Output must be a valid wire
00079     iter = circuit.Netlist.find(output);
00080     if (iter  ==  circuit.Netlist.end()) 
00081     {
00082         cout  << "Gate's output name %s does not represent a valid wire " << output << endl;
00083         return false;
00084     }
00085 
00086     // 2. If output type is PO, it should be
00087     // there in PO list
00088     if ((iter->second)->wtype == PO)
00089     {
00090         iter = circuit.PriOutputs.find(output);
00091         if (iter  ==  circuit.PriOutputs.end()) 
00092         {
00093             cout << "Gate's output name %s is supposedly PO but not present in PO list " << output << endl;
00094             return false;
00095         }
00096     }
00097 
00098     // Now that we are convinced, add the wire as gate's output
00099     // and the gate as wire's input :P
00100     Add_Gate_To_Wire_Input(circuit, gate,((iter->second)->id).c_str());
00101     gate->output = iter->second;
00102 
00103     while (numSignals--)
00104     {
00105 
00106 
00107         // Some consistency checks before we add
00108         // the wires to the gates inputs and output
00109         // 1. Input must be a valid wire
00110         iter = circuit.Netlist.find(inputs[numSignals]);
00111         if (iter  ==  circuit.Netlist.end()) 
00112         {
00113             cout << "Gate's input name %s does not represent a valid wire" << inputs[numSignals] << endl;
00114             return false;
00115         }
00116 
00117         // 2. If input type is PI, it should be
00118         // there in PI list
00119         if ((iter->second)->wtype == PI)
00120         {
00121             iter = circuit.PriInputs.find(inputs[numSignals]);
00122             if (iter  ==  circuit.PriInputs.end()) 
00123             {
00124                 cout << "Gate's input name %s is supposedly PI but not present in PI list" << inputs[numSignals] << endl;
00125                 return false;
00126             }
00127         }
00128 
00129         // Now that we are convinced, add the wire as gate's input
00130         gate->inputs.push_back(iter->second);
00131         Add_Gate_To_Wire_Output(circuit,gate,((iter->second)->id).c_str());
00132     }
00133 
00134     // Finally we add the gate to the circuit list
00135     gate->tempInputs = (gate->inputs).size();
00136     circuit.Gates.insert( pair<string,Gate *>(name, gate) );
00137 
00138     return true;
00139 }

00216 bool Resolve_Branches(Circuit& circuit)
00217 {
00218    map<string,Wire*>:: iterator iter = (circuit.Netlist).begin();
00219    cout << "Resolve Branches started" << endl;
00220    while (iter != (circuit.Netlist).end())
00221     {
00222         Wire* iwire = iter->second;
00223         
00224         // Condition for stemout
00225         // 1. If the wire is not a PO, output size is > 1
00226         // 2. If the wire is a PO output size is > 0
00227         if (  ( (int)(iwire->outputs).size() > 1 
00228             || ( (int) (iwire->outputs).size() > 0  && (iwire->wtype == PO))) 
00229             && (Wire_Not_Derived(iwire)))
00230         {
00231 
00232                 cout << "Calling resolve wire for  " << iwire->id << endl;
00233                 Resolve_Wire(circuit,iwire);
00234         }
00235         else 
00236         {
00237             cout << "No need to resolve wire " << iwire->id << endl;
00238         }
00239         iter++;
00240     }
00241     cout << "Resolve branches completed successfully" << endl << endl;
00242     return true;
00243 }

00247 void Resolve_Wire(Circuit&,Wire* wire)
00248 {
00249 
00250     // Assuming that initially all outputs of
00251     // a wire are gates
00252     //Steps:
00253     // 1. Find out if a wire has more than one outputs
00254     // 2. Create a new wire - with input as the orig wire
00255     // and output as the gate
00256     // 3. Update the orig wire's outputs to reflect the wires rather than gates
00257     // 4. Update the output gates (orig gates) inputs showing the new wires
00258     // as inputs
00259 
00260     cout << "Need to resolve wire:   " << wire->id << endl;
00261     list<Element*>:: iterator iter = (wire->outputs).begin();
00262     while ( iter != (wire->outputs).end() )
00263     {
00264         Element* curEle = (*iter);
00265         if (curEle->type == GATE)
00266         {
00267 
00268         Gate* gate = dynamic_cast<Gate*>(*iter);
00269         assert(gate); // dynamic_cast must not fail
00270         string newname = (wire->id)+"_"+(gate->id);
00271         newname = Check_Name_Present(circuit,newname);
00272         // step 2. Add a new wire for this instance
00273         cout << "Adding derived wire:    " <<  newname  << endl;
00274         Add_Wire(circuit,newname.c_str(),CONNECTION);
00275 
00276         // The new wire's output should be the 
00277         // gate
00278         Add_Gate_To_Wire_Output(circuit,gate,newname.c_str());
00279 
00280         // The new wire's input should be the old wire and
00281         // the old wire' output should change from gate to 
00282         // new wire
00283 
00284         Wire* newwire = ((circuit.Netlist).find(newname))->second;
00285         newwire->input = wire;
00286          // finally update the gate's inputlist
00287         (gate->inputs).remove(wire);
00288         (gate->inputs).push_back(newwire);
00289         
00290         (*iter) = newwire;
00291 
00292        iter++;
00293         }
00294 
00295 
00296         else continue;
00297     }
00298 
00299     if (wire->wtype == PO)
00300     {
00301         cout << "***************PO with fanout detected*************" <<  endl;
00302         assert(false);
00303     }
00304 }
